        - heading "I'm Matias." [level=2] [ref=e56]
        - paragraph [ref=e57]: "I know what it feels like to carry fear and self-doubt while trying to figure out who you are and where you're going — because I've lived it. My own path has taken me through some genuinely difficult lows, and through them, I learned something I now build my whole practice around: you don't have to come out as anything to be taken seriously, anywhere, by anyone — including yourself. Every reinvention I've lived — from Poland to Spain to Sydney, from journalism to banking to coaching — taught me that growth doesn't happen despite our struggles. It happens through them."
        - paragraph [ref=e58]: "That work of becoming who you are doesn't happen in isolation. Whether leading transformation at Santander Group and BBVA, or sitting with someone ready to rewrite their story, I've always been drawn to the same question: how do you navigate the unknown? Being named a Santander Group Young Leader in 2024 reminded me that strategic clarity and deep empathy aren't opposites — they come from the same place. And yes — as a gay man, this is personal for me too. Career, confidence, purpose: they're all connected, because you are."
        - paragraph [ref=e59]: "Today, I help people walk the path I had to walk myself: facing fear, learning to belong to yourself, and building a life that actually feels like yours. Wherever you're starting from, you belong here. Let's discover your next chapter, together."
